  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yes, but that goes into the push function which is then later stopped as the router is already disposed: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/0820455ad291fb3e1910ebdfbcfa8d18eb811d31/packages/react-instantsearch-nextjs/src/InstantSearchNext.tsx#L86-L95\r\n\r\nI do think in general that it's not a bad idea to add `this.write({})` inside an option (default to true), called `cleanup` or similar. If you have that write removed, does everything work as expected? I'm happy to review a PR for it",
